            <pb facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#b">Humboldt and the Letter Writers.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <milestone unit="section" rendition="#hr"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <div n="2">
                    <p>Berlin papers received at the City<lb break="yes"/>of Baltimore contain the
                        following card<lb break="yes"/>from Alexander Von Humboldt:</p>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <dateline>
                        <hi rendition="#et">
                            <hi rendition="#k">Berlin,</hi> March 15, 1859.</hi>
                    </dateline>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <p>&#x201C;Suffering beneath the pressure of a<lb break="yes"/>still increasing
                        correspondence, amount-<lb break="no"/>ing to between sixteen hundred and<lb
                            break="yes"/>two thousand communications per an-<lb break="no"/>num, and
                        embracing letters, printed<lb break="yes"/>pamphlets on matters with which
                            I<lb break="yes"/>am wholly unacquainted, manuscripts<lb break="yes"
                        />concerning which my opinion is desir-<lb break="no"/>ed, projects for
                        emigration and colon-<lb break="no"/>izing, the sending of models,
                            machines<lb break="yes"/>and natural curiosities, requests of con-<lb
                            break="no"/>tributions to collections of
                                <choice><sic>authographs</sic><corr type="editorial"
                                >autographs,</corr></choice><lb break="yes"/>offers to take charge
                        of my domestic<lb break="yes"/>concerns, to cheer and enliven me,
                            &#x0026;c..<lb break="yes"/>&#x0026;c. I must again publicly urge all<lb
                            break="yes"/>persons having my welfare at heart, to<lb break="yes"
                        />exert their influence in my behalf, that<lb break="yes"/>individuals in
                        both continents may no<lb break="yes"/>longer busy themselves with my
                            person<lb break="yes"/>and make of my house an intelligence<lb
                            break="yes"/>office; and that I be allowed, in the<lb break="yes"
                        />declining state of my physical and<lb break="yes"/>mental powers, to enjoy
                        some rest and<lb break="yes"/>leisure to attend to my duties. May<lb
                            break="yes"/>this cry of relief, which I utter with<lb break="yes"/>much
                        reluctance and after reflection,<lb break="yes"/>not meet an unfriendly
                        interpretation!</p>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <closer>
                        <salute>
                            <hi rendition="#et">A. <hi rendition="#k">Von
                                Humboldt.</hi>&#x201D;</hi>
                        </salute>
                    </closer>
                </div>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <lb break="yes"/>
